## Suggested Database Schema

```
conversations
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ id
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ type          (direct, case, group)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ case_id       (nullable, FK ‚Üí cases)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ name          (nullable, for group channels)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ created_at
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ updated_at

conversation_user (pivot)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ conversation_id
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ user_id
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ last_read_at  (for read receipts)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ is_muted
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ joined_at

messages
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ id
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ conversation_id (FK ‚Üí conversations)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ user_id         (FK ‚Üí users, sender)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ body            (text content)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ type            (text, file, system)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ parent_id       (nullable, for replies/threads)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ metadata        (JSON ‚Äî file info, mentions, etc.)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ created_at
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ updated_at
```

### Key Design Decisions

- **Polymorphic conversations**: One `conversations` table handles 1:1, case-linked, and group chats via the `type` column
- **Read tracking** is per-user via `last_read_at` on the pivot ‚Äî unread count = messages after this timestamp
- **File sharing** reuses the existing [Document](file:///d:/xampp/htdocs/xiromile3/xiromile-app/app/Models/Document.php#9-170) model; the message `metadata` JSON stores the `document_id`
- **@Mentions** are parsed from message `body` and stored in `metadata` for notification dispatch

