---

## Hosting Considerations (cPanel)

| Concern | Solution |
|---|---|
| No WebSocket support | Use **Livewire polling** (`wire:poll.3s`) for near-real-time |
| Database performance | Add indexes on `conversation_id`, `user_id`, `created_at` |
| File uploads in chat | Reuse existing `DocumentUploadController` logic |
| SQLite limitations | Works fine for small teams; recommend MySQL for 10+ concurrent users |

---

## Summary

For your CA practice management app, live messaging would significantly improve team coordination. I recommend:

1. **Start with Phase 1** (1:1 DMs + conversation list + unread badges) using **Livewire polling**
2. Then add **Phase 2** (case discussions + @mentions + file sharing) to deeply integrate messaging with your case/task workflow
3. **Phase 3** is nice-to-have and can be added based on user feedback

> [!TIP]
> The biggest value for your specific domain is **Case Discussion Threads** (Phase 2) ‚Äî having a chat linked to each case where all stakeholders can discuss eliminates scattered WhatsApp/email threads and keeps all communication auditable within the app.

